ianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Greater Conjuration: Earth (49) vs Invoke Death (49)</span><hr size=1> I was curious as to how well my GC:Earth would stack up against the level 49 necro pet, Invoke Death.<br>
<br>
Both pets are level 41.  Invoke Death has about 2350hp, quads for 55, lifetaps for 25 I think, kicks and bashes.  GC:Earth has about 2650hp, quads for 56, and I'm pretty sure you guys know the rest.<br>
<br>
So I summon it armor and cast Burnout3 on it and off they go.  With 300 more hp and summoned plate armor, I expect my Earthen fellow to win with at least 15-20% health left.<br>
<br>
Clock is ticking...<br>
<br>
Earth pet wins with 4% health left.  Holy cow!  Invoke Death, I must say, is one MEANASS pet for its level.  I'm also taking into consideration that necros don't get a tanking upgrade until 59 (EoT), so I'm not calling a nerf here.  <br>
<br>
I'm merely posting this to share my curiositie's findings.  How well does Legacy of Zek stand up to Ward of Xegony? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marloon>Marloon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/02 5:38:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well..</span><hr size=1>  Well the earth pet is by far the worst pet at this level.  Try using a fire pet, and that skele will be eaten alive.  Or wait one level and try the lvl 50 MSII pet against it.  even though that spell is one level above 49, it still is the same level pet.  It just has the hit points of a earth with the damage of a water/air, and sometimes teh ds of a fire.<br>
<br>
Marloon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archangelranari@themagicianstower>Archangel Ranari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/02 5:45:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well..</span><hr size=1> I've got my hands on the 49 air pet also (/thanks bazaar), which is the only style pet I have a focus item for (/thanks bazaar again!).  I'll brush my focused 49 air pet up against that skeleton's trousers and see what happens.<br>
<br>
So far though, I've been using strictly my 49 air pet due to the only available the focus item in my inventory.  I'm pretty sure a 49 fire vs 49 necro pet duel would be ghastly obvious who the victor would be.  Being reemed back with 42pts of damage for every hit would certainly add up REALLY fast no matter how much hp/ac one has. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=limpylionbait>LimpyLionBait</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 243<br> <font color=#333333>(12/26/02 9:06:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=876.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well..</span><hr size=1> The problem with the earth pet is that it cant dodge worth squat. It will get hit constantly. The only advantage to this is that it makes shield of lava that much more effective. If you're going to duel pet vs pet without a ds, then earth is not the way to go. Air is the best tank by far of our pet types - that stun is not to be taken lightly :P Armor it up and its even better. Grab some gnoll hide lariats for that extra oomph - the more stuns, the merrier it gets. <br>
<br>
Fire pet is of course very effective, although after 1 fight with that the necro may cry foul and ask you not to use a ds'ing pet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Always armor up your pets for that extra ac - its our skill, so use it. Summon the pet 2 weapons first, so that you can equip a elemental defender in the back slot (with no weapons it will try to use it in the shield slot), then give the plate armor.<br>
<br>
Also make sure to hold your temple of Sol Ro focus item in your primary when summoning - those extra stats are worth it (49 and under pets I mean)<br>
<br>
Limpy<br>
